parameters.name: EndTimestamp
parameters.description: The end time. This value is a UNIX timestamp.

parameters.name: EntityType
parameters.description:
The type of log to obtain. Valid values:

- **PV\_ZONE**: operation logs of built-in authoritative zones.

- **PV\_RECORD**: operation logs of DNS records.

- **RESOLVER\_RULE**: operation logs of forwarding rules.

- **CUSTOM\_LINE**: operation logs of custom lines.

- **RESOLVER\_ENDPOINT**: operation logs of outbound endpoints.

- **INBOUND\_ENDPOINT**: operation logs of inbound endpoints.

- **CACHE\_RESERVE\_DOMAIN**: operation logs of domains for which cache is retained.

> If you specify another value, this parameter is ignored and logs of all types are returned.

parameters.name: Keyword
parameters.description: The keyword, such as a behavior or content. Fuzzy search is supported. The keyword is not case-sensitive.

parameters.name: Lang
parameters.description:
The language of the response. Valid values:

- zh: Chinese.

- en: English.

Default value: en

parameters.name: PageNumber
parameters.description: The number of the page to return. The value must be an integer that is greater than 0. Default value: 1.

parameters.name: PageSize
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page. Maximum value: 100. Default value: 20.

parameters.name: StartTimestamp
parameters.description: The start time. This value is a UNIX timestamp.

parameters.name: UserClientIp
parameters.description: The IP address of the user.

parameters.name: ZoneId
parameters.description:
The ID of the zone. - If you specify this parameter, the operation returns the change logs of DNS records for the specified zone.
- If you leave this parameter empty, the operation returns the change logs of all zones and DNS records that belong to the current account.
